  "summary": "dotenvv-tool postinstall exfiltrates host and filesystem data over HTTP",
  "details": "The postinstall.js script executed automatically on `npm install` reads host identity information (os.hostname(), os.userInfo(), os.homedir()) and probes the filesystem via multiple fs.existsSync() calls, then transmits the collected data via an http request. The package name is a typosquat of the widely-used `dotenv` / `dotenv-tool` family, and the install-time behavior harvests installer host data without any legitimate build or configuration purpose — a standard credential/environment reconnaissance shape for a malicious npm package.",
